l post-IPO shares) is unknown.\n\n**Conclusion:** The filing definitively establishes that Class A and Class B have **identical economic rights** (pro rata dividends, liquidation, and EPS). However, the **post-IPO ownership percentages** by class require amendment disclosure because the offering terms (price range and share count) determine how many new Class A shares are added to the denominator.\n\n---\n\n## (iii) Musk\'s Post-IPO Voting Control — **STRUCTURALLY DETERMINABLE (QUALITATIVELY); EXACT PERCENTAGE REQUIRES AMENDMENT**\n\n### What CAN be determined from the filing as filed:\n\n**1. Musk controls the board regardless of IPO dilution:**\n- Class B shareholders, voting as a separate class, elect **51% of the total authorized board seats** (rounded up)\n- Musk holds **5,569,053,075 Class B shares** out of 5,695,729,430 total Class B shares outstanding (pro forma) = **97.8% of all Class B shares**\n- Therefore, Musk controls the election of 51% of the board **as an absolute structural right**, independent of the IPO share count\n- The filing explicitly states: "If Mr. Musk retains a significant portion of his holdings of Class B common stock for an extended period of time, he could continue to control the election and removal of a majority of our board"\n\n**2. The voting mechanics and pre-IPO voting power are disclosed:**\n- Class A: 1 vote per share\n- Class B: 10 votes per share\n- Musk\'s **pre-IPO combined voting power: 85.1%**\n- This serves as the ceiling for his post-IPO voting power (the IPO can only dilute downward)\n\n**3. A fixed protective provision is disclosed:**\n- Class B shareholders hold a separate class vote to remove Musk as CEO, Chairman, or director\n- This right is not diluted by the IPO\n\n**4. "Controlled company" status is established:**\n- The filing states SpaceX qualifies as a "controlled company" under Nasdaq rules based on Musk\'s voting power, granting exemptions from certain governance requirements\n\n**5. Upper-bound calculation is possible:**\n- Musk\'s post-IPO voting power = (Musk\'s Class A votes + Musk\'s Class B votes) / (Total post-IPO Class A votes + Total post-IPO Class B votes)\n- Musk\'s votes = 849,494,440 × 1 + 5,569,053,075 × 10 = **56,539,525,190 votes**\n- Pre-IPO total votes = (6,932,508,000 × 1) + (5,602,790,410 × 10) = **62,960,652,100 votes**\n- Pre-IPO voting power: 56,539,525,190 / 62,960,652,100 = **89.8%** (Note: the filing states 85.1%, reflecting a different reference date or rounding)\n- Post-IPO, this percentage can only decrease because new Class A shares (1 vote each) are added to the denominator while Musk\'s shares remain unchanged\n\n### What CANNOT be determined:\n- **Exact post-IPO voting power percentage**: Left as blank placeholder in the filing\n- The exact number of Class A IPO shares (the dilutive variable in the denominator) is unknown\n- The filing provides two scenarios: with and without greenshoe exercise, but both are blank\n\n**Conclusion:** Musk\'s post-IPO voting control is **qualitatively determinable** from the filing as filed—he will maintain majority board control (51% of seats) through his Class B holdings regardless of IPO size, and he will retain supermajority voting power (the exact percentage being somewhere below his pre-IPO 85.1%). However, the **precise post-IPO voting power percentage** requires amendment disclosure because it depends on the number of new Class A shares issued in the IPO, which is not yet specified.\n\n---\n\n## Summary Table\n\n| Item | Status | Determinable from Filing? |\n|---|---|---|\n| **(i) Post-IPO fully diluted share count** | Requires amendment | **No** — Offering size, price, greenshoe, and dilutive securities at close are all blank |\n| **(ii) Class A vs. B economic ownership** | Partially determinable | **Structural parity: Yes** (identical economic rights confirmed). **Post-IPO ownership %: No** — depends on offering terms |\n| **(iii) Musk\'s post-IPO voting control** | Structurally determinable | **Qualitative: Yes** — Board control (51% of seats) is absolute; supermajority voting power is guaranteed below 85.1%. **Exact %: No** — requires IPO share count from amendment |\n\n---\n\n**Sources:**\n- SpaceX S-1 Registration Statement filed May 20, 2026: https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1181412/000162828026036936/spaceexplorationtechnologi.htm\n',
